## Project Layout
> Single source of truth for where project artifacts live. Every skill resolves artifact paths
> from THIS table instead of hardcoding them. When a doc moves, change its row here only —
> `design-sync` keeps this honest at each merge. Skill-internal files (each skill's own
> `templates/`, `references/`, `examples/`, `scripts/`) are NOT listed here; they stay inside the
> skill folder wherever the agent loads skills from, and never move under `docs/`.

| Artifact | Path |
|----------|------|
| AGENTS.md (this file) | `AGENTS.md` (repo root) |
| Architecture | `docs/architecture.md` |
| Data model | `docs/data-model.md` |
| Tech stack | `docs/tech-stack.md` |
| Testing strategy | `docs/testing-strategy.md` |
| UI conventions | `docs/ui-conventions.md` |
| ADRs | `docs/adr/ADR-NNN-*.md` |
| API contracts | `docs/api-contracts/*.openapi.yaml` |
| Design history (proposals) | `docs/design-history/` |
| Design changelog | `docs/CHANGELOG-design.md` |
| PRD | `docs/product/PRD.md` |
| Epics | `docs/product/epics.md` |
| Epic map | `docs/product/epic-map.json` |
| Per-epic folder | `docs/product/epics/<EPIC_KEY>/` |
| Stories list | `docs/product/epics/<EPIC_KEY>/_epic/stories.md` |
| Story map | `docs/product/epics/<EPIC_KEY>/_epic/story-map.json` |
| Epic sequence | `docs/product/epics/<EPIC_KEY>/_epic/epic-sequence.md` + `.json` |
| Per-story folder | `docs/product/epics/<EPIC_KEY>/stories/<STORY_KEY>/` |
| Story design note | `…/stories/<STORY_KEY>/story-design.md` |
| Test plan | `…/stories/<STORY_KEY>/test-plan.md` |
| Verification report | `…/stories/<STORY_KEY>/verification.md` |
| Code-review report | `…/stories/<STORY_KEY>/code-review.md` |
| Design-sync note | `…/stories/<STORY_KEY>/design-sync.md` |
| Product overview | `docs/product-overview.md` |

> **Per-story folder rule:** every artifact for one story lives in its own folder
> `docs/product/epics/<EPIC_KEY>/stories/<STORY_KEY>/` with short, un-suffixed filenames (the
> folder carries the key). Resolve a story's artifacts under that folder only. Use
> `docs/product/epic-map.json` to find a story's epic if you only have the story key.

